        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 2:07PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 207 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sanford, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lillington, Lemon Springs, Gum Springs, Holly Springs, Broadway,
Raven Rock State Park, Olivia, Sanford, Harris Lake Boat Launch, and
Seminole.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
